{"source_key":"sha256-61160046d0da1392acf2cac155d2870d","record_index":233,"record_hash":"sha256:b3ea40242c8dbe1f4ca211120e1bc4ef9e9e261b0c5ec4e8bfac3812b2e9a71c","timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:11:09.700Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_kind":"file_edit","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: crates/but/skill/STALE_INVENTORY.md\n+# GitButler CLI Skill Staleness Inventory\n+\n+Date: 2026-05-29\n+\n+Scope checked:\n+\n+- Skill content: `crates/but/skill/SKILL.md`, `references/reference.md`, `references/concepts.md`, `references/examples.md`\n+- Development docs with skill assumptions: `crates/but/skill/README.md`, `crates/but/skill/RESEARCH.md`\n+- Current CLI API: `crates/but/src/args/*.rs`, `crates/but/src/lib.rs`, command implementations, and `cargo run -q -p but -- --help` plus targeted `target/debug/but <command> --help`\n+\n+This is only an inventory. Do not treat it as a fix list already applied.\n+\n+## High Priority Stale Items\n+\n+| Area | Current skill text | Current CLI reality | Update needed |\n+| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n+| `--status-after` blanket rule | `SKILL.md` says \"Always add `--status-after` to mutation commands\" and the core flow says `but <mutation> ... --status-after`. | `--status-after` is global in clap help, but only actually wraps output for `clean`, `rub`, `commit`/`commit empty`, `absorb`, `uncommit`, `amend`, `stage`, `squash`, and top-level `move`. It is ignored by many mutations: `branch new/delete`, `pull`, `push`, `pr`, `reword`, `discard`, `resolve`, `apply`, `unapply`, `mark`, `unmark`, `merge`, `pick`, `setup`, `teardown`, `oplog restore/snapshot`, `alias`, `config`, `skill`, `update`. | Replace the blanket rule with a supported-command list. For unsupported mutations, tell agents to run `but status -fv` after the command if they need fresh IDs/state. |\n+| Pull recipe | `SKILL.md` says `but pull --check` then `but pull --status-after`. | `but pull --status-after` parses, but `pull` does not call the status-after wrapper. | Change to `but pull --check`, then `but pull`, then `but status -fv` if state is needed. |\n+| `but apply` identifiers | `reference.md`, `concepts.md`, and examples use `but apply <id>` / `but apply bv`. | Top-level `but apply` takes a branch ref/name string. It resolves exact refs and a unique bare remote branch name, but does not resolve CLI IDs through `IdMap`. `but unapply` does accept stack/branch CLI IDs. | Update apply docs and examples to use branch names or refs, not CLI IDs. Keep CLI-ID guidance only for `unapply`. |\n+| Empty commit messages | `concepts.md` and `examples.md` use `but commit empty -m \"TODO: Add error handling\"`. | `commit empty` explicitly rejects `--message`, `--message-file`, branch positional args, `--create`, `--only`, `--all`, `--no-hooks`, `--ai`, `--diff`, and `--no-diff`. Empty commits have no message by default; use `but reword` afterward. | Replace all `commit empty -m ...` examples with `but commit empty [target|--before|--after]`, then `but reword <empty-commit-id> -m \"...\"`. |\n+| Reorder recipe | `SKILL.md` says run `but move <commit-a> <commit-b>`, refresh IDs, then run the inverse `but move <commit-b> <commit-a>`. | Current `but move` performs the move in one command. Running the inverse is not a normal refresh step and can undo or alter the intended order. | Remove the inverse-move instruction. Tell agents to refresh status only if they need new IDs. |\n+| JSON shape in research docs | `RESEARCH.md` expects `--json` on all commands and mocks command output like `{\"result\":{\"commitId\":\"abc123\"}}` and branch creation as `{\"branchId\":\"bv\",\"name\":\"...\"}`. | Current JSON output is mixed. Status JSON is camelCase (`unassignedChanges`, `assignedChanges`, etc.), but mutation result payloads are often snake_case or minimal: regular commit returns `commit_id`, `branch`, `branch_tip`; `commit empty` returns `commit_id`; branch new returns `branch` and optional `anchor`; many rub/stage/move paths return `{\"ok\": true}`. With `--status-after`, JSON is wrapped as `{\"result\": <mutation_output>, \"status\": <workspace_status>}` or `{\"result\": ..., \"status_error\": \"...\"}`. | Update `RESEARCH.md` mocks and metrics if those evals are still meant to run. Decide whether mandatory `--json` is still policy; `SKILL.md` no longer says it, but `RESEARCH.md` still scores it. |\n+\n+## Missing Current API Coverage\n+\n+These are not necessarily wrong examples, but the skill reference is behind the current CLI.\n+\n+| Command/area | Missing or incomplete coverage |\n+| --- | --- |\n+| Global options | `reference.md` should document `-j, --json` and `-f, --format <human|shell|json|none>`, plus `-C, --current-dir <PATH>`. It currently only lists `--status-after`, `-C`, and help. |\n+| `but status` | Missing `--refresh-prs` / `-r` and `--no-hint`. |\n+| `but diff` | Missing `--tui` and `--no-tui`; `but config ui set tui true/false` controls the default. |\n+| `but stage` | Current command supports interactive TUI mode: `but stage` and `but stage --branch <branch>`, plus direct `but stage <file-or-hunk> <branch>`. Docs only cover direct file staging and should say file-or-hunk. |\n+| `but branch new` | Branch name is optional; with no name the CLI generates a canned branch name. Docs show it as required. |\n+| `but branch list` | Missing `--empty`. |\n+| `but branch delete` | Parser has no `--force`, despite the command help text mentioning one. Skill does not currently mention `--force`, so avoid adding it unless the CLI gains it. |\n+| `but commit` | Missing `--diff` and `--no-diff`; JSON mode requires `-m`, `--message-file`, or `--ai` for regular commits. |\n+| `but commit empty` | Missing no-arg form (`but commit empty`) and positional target form (`but commit empty <target>`), both defaulting to before/top behavior depending on arguments. |\n+| `but move` | Current source can be comma-separated selectors for multi-commit moves (`but move c1,c2 target`). Docs only show one source. |\n+| `but resolve` | Missing `but resolve cancel --force` / `-f`. |\n+| `but push` | `--with-force` / `-f` defaults to true in args, so listing it as the way to force-push is misleading. Docs also miss `--no-verify` alias for `--no-hooks`. |\n+| `but pr` | Missing aliases `but mr` and `but review`; top-level `--draft`; `pr new --draft`; `--skip-force-push-protection`; `--no-verify` alias; and subcommands `auto-merge`, `set-draft`, `set-ready`. The selector syntax for those subcommands accepts branch names, branch IDs, stack IDs, or review numeric IDs, comma-separated. |\n+| `but oplog` | Missing `oplog list --since`, `oplog list --snapshot`, and `oplog snapshot [-m <message>]`. |\n+| `but redo` | Visible top-level command but absent from the skill reference/concepts. |\n+| `but tui` | Visible top-level command but absent from `reference.md`. |\n+| `but config` | Reference only says `but config`; it should cover `user`, `forge`, `target`, `metrics`, `ui`, and `ai` subcommands, including AI providers `openai`, `anthropic`, `ollama`, `lmstudio`, and `openrouter`. |\n+| `but update` | `but update` now requires a subcommand. Current subcommands are `check`, `suppress [days]`, and on supported builds `install [nightly|release|version]`. `reference.md` says just `but update`. |\n+| `but alias` | Reference only says `but alias`; it should cover `list`, `add <name> <value> [-g]`, `remove|rm <name> [-g]`. |\n+| `but gui` | Missing optional `[PATH]` and visible alias `but .`. |\n+| `but skill` | `README.md` is current enough, but `reference.md` omits `skill install --global/--path/--detect` and `skill check --global/--local/--update`. |\n+| Hidden-but-mentioned commands | `but completions <shell>` is hidden but still mentioned by top-level help and examples. If references keep it, mark it as a utility/hidden command. |\n+\n+## Terminology and Concept Cleanup\n+\n+- The skill description advertises \"stash work\" and says it replaces `git stash`, but there is no `but stash` command. The closest workflow is usually `but unapply` / `but apply` for applied branches, or branch assignment/commit operations for work-in-progress. Clarify this instead of implying a direct command replacement.\n+- Several docs use \"unstaged\" loosely. Current status JSON distinguishes `unassignedChanges` from per-stack `assignedChanges`; human output says \"unassigned changes\". Prefer \"unassigned\" when referring to `zz`.\n+- `reference.md` says `--status-after` is supported on `rub`, `commit`, `stage`, `amend`, `absorb`, `squash`, `move`, and `uncommit`, but it omits `clean`. It also does not warn that the globally accepted flag is ignored elsewhere.\n+- `RESEARCH.md` is out of sync with the installed skill policy. It still treats `but status --json` before mutations and `--json --status-after` on mutations as hard metrics, while `SKILL.md` currently teaches `but status -fv` and human-readable flows.\n+\n+## Current Visible CLI Surface Snapshot\n+\n+Top-level visible commands from current help:\n+\n+- Inspection: `status`, `diff`, `show`\n+- Branching/committing: `commit`, `stage`, `branch`, `merge`, `discard`, `resolve`, `unapply`, `apply`, `clean`, `pick`\n+- Editing commits: `rub`, `absorb`, `reword`, `uncommit`, `amend`, `squash`, `move`\n+- Operation history: `oplog`, `undo`, `redo`\n+- Server interactions: `push`, `pull`, `pr` (aliases: `mr`, `review`)\n+- Rules: `mark`, `unmark`\n+- Other: `setup`, `teardown`, `gui` (alias: `.`), `tui`, `update`, `alias`, `config`, `skill`\n+\n+Status-after implementation, based on `crates/but/src/lib.rs`:\n+\n+- Actually emits appended/wrapped status: `clean`, `rub`, `commit`, `commit empty`, `absorb`, `uncommit`, `amend`, `stage`, `squash`, `move`\n+- Accepted but not currently wired to append status for most other commands due the global clap flag\n+\n+Useful current JSON shapes to keep in mind:\n+\n+```json\n+{\n+  \"result\": { \"commit_id\": \"...\", \"branch\": \"...\", \"branch_tip\": \"...\" },\n+  \"status\": {\n+    \"unassignedChanges\": [],\n+    \"stacks\": [],\n+    \"mergeBase\": {},\n+    \"upstreamState\": {}\n+  }\n+}\n+```\n+\n+The exact `result` object varies by mutation. Do not assume camelCase there unless the specific command uses a camelCase DTO.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-29T14:11:09.700Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}